HEADWORD: Gaultheria
<hw>Gaul*the"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of ericaceous shrubs with evergreen
foliage, and, often, edible berries. It includes the American
winter-green (<spn>Gaultheria procumbens</spn>), and the larger-fruited
<stype>salal</stype> of Northwestern America (<spn>Gaultheria
Shallon</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>gaumless</ent>⟦br⟧
